data.enText: without an end; existing or continuing forever
the promise of eternal life in heaven

data.chText: 她是个永远的乐观主义者。
data.enText: She's an eternal optimist (= she always expects that the best will happen) .
eternal truths (= ideas that are always true and never change)

data.chText: 无休止的；永不停止的；没完没了的
data.enText: happening often and seeming never to stop

data.chText: 我烦透了你们那没完没了的争论。
data.enText: I'm tired of your eternal arguments.
I'll be eternally grateful to you for this.
women trying to look eternally young

example: the ageless themes of love and revenge

value.def: Something that is eternal lasts for ever.

example.ex: Whoever believes in Him shall have eternal life.
example.tran: 所有相信上帝的人都会获得永生。

example.ex: She is eternally grateful to her family for their support...
example.tran: 她永远感激家人们给予她的支持。

example.ex: The whole universe exists eternally in that one infinite being.
example.tran: 整个宇宙在无限的空间中永生。

value.def: If you describe something as eternal, you mean that it seems to last for ever, often because you think it is boring or annoying.

example.ex: In the background was that eternal hum.
example.tran: 背景音是没完没了的嗡嗡声。

value.def: Eternal truths, values, and questions never change and are believed to be always true and to be relevant in all situations.

example.ex: ...the eternal truths of the Indian subcontinent.
example.tran: 印度次大陆的永恒真理

value.tran: （真理、价值、问题等）永恒的，不朽的

trans: 永恒回归；永劫回归；永恒轮回
怡亚通；链股份有限公司
围棋的长生劫；来世，永生
永恒荣耀；永恒的荣耀；永垂不朽；永恒的荣誉
